Legs (
Figs. 21–24
). All legs tridactylous with stronger median and slender lateral claws. Formulas of leg setation and solenidia: I (
1–4 – 3–4 – 20
) [ 1–2 – 2 ], II (
1–4 – 3–4 – 15
) [ 1 – 1–2 ], III (
1–2 – 1–3 – 15
) [ 1 – 1 –0], IV (
1– 2 – 2–3 – 12
) [ 0–1 –0]; homology of setae and solenidia indicated in
Table 1
. Almost all setae distinctly barbed; some ventral setae of tarsi and tibiae with long cilia. Solenidia ω 1 and ω 2 on tarsi II, σ on genua III straight or weakly curved, rod-like. Other solenidia rather long, setiform.

Several diagnostic keys for the species of
Pilizetes
have been published (see
Balogh 1960
;
Mahunka 1984
;
Balogh and Balogh 2002
).
